    • Content

      * Model 1a, lottery EUT
* maximum likelihood estimation of risk attitudes (CRRA utility) under EUT 
* U(x) = (x^(1-r))/(1-r)
* allows for subjects to make structural error in the comparison of the two EUs
* (Harrison, List, Towe; Econometrica 2007)

clear all
cd "C:\Documents and Settings\Redzo\Desktop\current Research\risk aversion"
capture log close
log using lotteryEUT.log, replace
use lottery.dta, clear

* Note left = A, right=B


program define ML_lotteryEUT
args lnf r noise

tempvar c prob1l prob2l prob1r prob2r m1 m2 m3 m4 u1 u2 u3 u4 euL euR euDiff

gen double `c' = $ML_y1
gen double `prob1l' = $ML_y2
gen double `prob2l' = $ML_y3
gen double `prob1r' = $ML_y4
gen double `prob2r' = $ML_y5

gen double `m1' = $ML_y6
gen double `m2' = $ML_y7
gen double `m3' = $ML_y8
gen double `m4' = $ML_y9

gen double `u1' = (`m1'^(1-`r'))/(1-`r')
gen double `u2' = (`m2'^(1-`r'))/(1-`r')
gen double `u3' = (`m3'^(1-`r'))/(1-`r')
gen double `u4' = (`m4'^(1-`r'))/(1-`r')

gen double `euL' = (`prob1l'*`u1') + (`prob2l'*`u2')
gen double `euR' = (`prob1r'*`u3') + (`prob2r'*`u4')

generate double `euDiff' = (`euL'-`euR')/`noise'

* evaluate the likelihood
quietly replace `lnf' = ln(normal(`euDiff')) if `c'==1
quietly replace `lnf' = ln(1-normal(`euDiff')) if `c'==0

end
ml model lf ML_lotteryEUT (r: c prob1l prob2l prob1r prob2r m1 m2 m3 m4 = dem_age dem_econ dem_female dem_stats dem_uniyear) (noise:), cluster(id) technique(nr) 
ml check
ml search
ml maximize, difficult

ml graph
